{
  "texts": [
    "DPO implicitly learns token-level rewards.",
    "In RLHF, rewards are typically assigned at the end of sequences, which can extend to thousands of tokens.",
    "However, not all tokens contribute equally to the final reward (Chan et al., 2024; Rafailov et al., 2024; Yang et al., 2024a).",
    "To address this, it is crucial for a preference optimization algorithm to effectively distribute sequencelevel rewards across individual tokens.",
    "Previous work (Zhong et al., 2024; Rafailov et al., 2024) has shown that Direct Preference Optimization (DPO; Rafailov et al. 2023) implicitly learns tokenlevel rewards under sequence-level reward supervision."
  ]
}